Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida, announcing the establishment of the United States Space Command. This new combatant command will oversee all military activities in space and will be the 11th combatant command in the U.S. military. Pence also mentioned that President Donald Trump will sign a new space policy directive to create the U.S. Space Force, the sixth branch of the armed forces, before the end of 2020. The vice president praised the work of the 45th Space Wing and emphasized the importance of American leadership in space. He also referenced the historic Apollo 8 mission and the astronauts' message about the creation of the Earth. Pence concluded his speech by thanking the military, industry partners, and all those involved in the space enterprise.